HEADWORD: Dicksoniaceae
<hw>Dicksoniaceae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A family of
plants comprising the tree ferns; it includes the genera
<gen>Dicksonia</gen>; <gen>Cibotium</gen>; <gen>Culcita</gen>; and
<gen>Thyrsopteris</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Dicksoniaceae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
